TOPICS COVERED (MACHINE LEARNING PIPELINES & MODEL DEPLOYMENT)
Introduction to Model Deployment

The training session began with an introduction to Model Deployment, the final stage of the Machine Learning lifecycle where a trained model is made available for real-world use. Learned that after developing and evaluating a Machine Learning model, it must be deployed so that users or applications can make predictions using new data.

The trainer explained that deployment bridges the gap between model development and practical implementation. Discussed how deployed models are used in banking systems, healthcare applications, e-commerce platforms, recommendation systems, fraud detection, and mobile applications.

Machine Learning Workflow Review

Revised the complete Machine Learning pipeline from data collection to deployment.

The workflow included:

Problem Definition
Data Collection
Data Preprocessing
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Feature Engineering
Model Selection
Model Training
Model Evaluation
Hyperparameter Tuning
Model Deployment
Model Monitoring and Maintenance

Understood that each stage contributes to building a reliable and accurate Machine Learning application.

Introduction to Machine Learning Pipelines

Received a detailed explanation of Machine Learning Pipelines, which automate multiple Machine Learning tasks into a single workflow.

Learned that pipelines combine:

Data Preprocessing
Feature Scaling
Feature Encoding
Model Training
Prediction

into one reusable process.

The trainer explained that pipelines reduce coding errors, improve code readability, and ensure consistent preprocessing during both training and prediction.

