Making predictions using the pipeline.

Observed how pipelines simplify the Machine Learning workflow by executing all preprocessing and prediction steps automatically.

Saving Machine Learning Models

Learned the importance of saving trained Machine Learning models for future use.

Studied two commonly used serialization libraries:

Pickle

Learned how Pickle stores trained Machine Learning models in binary format.

Performed:

Saving trained models.
Loading saved models.
Reusing models without retraining.
Joblib

Received an introduction to Joblib.

Learned that Joblib is optimized for saving large Machine Learning models efficiently.

Compared Pickle and Joblib and discussed situations where each library is preferred.

Loading Pre-trained Models

Practiced loading previously saved Machine Learning models.

Performed:

Loading serialized models.
Providing new input data.
Making predictions without retraining.

Understood how model serialization reduces computational time in real-world applications.

